# Telco CRM — Data & Persistence

## JPA / Hibernate Configuration

- `spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto` must always be set to **`validate`**. Never use `create`, `create-drop`, or `update` in any environment.
- Schema changes are managed exclusively by **Flyway**. The JPA setting only verifies that the schema matches the entity model at startup.
- `spring.jpa.show-sql` may be `true` in development config; ensure it is `false` (or overridden) in production profiles.

## Flyway Migrations

- Migration scripts live in each service under `src/main/resources/db/migration/`.
- Naming convention: `V{version}__{description}.sql` (e.g., `V1__create_customer_table.sql`).
- Never modify a migration script that has already been applied. Always create a new versioned script.
- Each service's Flyway configuration must point to its own dedicated database URL.

## Entity Conventions

- All JPA entities must extend `BaseEntity` from `common-persistence`.
- Use `UUID` as the primary key type for all entities.
- Map enum columns with `@Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)`. Never use `EnumType.ORDINAL`.
- Use `OffsetDateTime` for all timestamp fields. Never use `java.util.Date` or `java.sql.Timestamp`.

```java
// ✅ GOOD
@Entity
public class Customer extends BaseEntity {

    @Id
    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.UUID)
    private UUID id;

    @Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)
    @Column(nullable = false)
    private CustomerType type; // INDIVIDUAL | CORPORATE

    @Column(name = "deleted_at")
    private OffsetDateTime deletedAt; // soft delete
}

// ❌ BAD
@Enumerated(EnumType.ORDINAL) // breaks on enum reordering
private CustomerType type;
private Date createdAt; // avoid java.util.Date
```

## Soft Delete

- `Customer` must use soft delete only. Set `deletedAt = now()` on deletion; never issue a `DELETE` SQL statement for customer records.
- Repositories querying customers must filter `WHERE deleted_at IS NULL` by default (use `@Where` or a `Specification`).

## DTO Mapping — MapStruct

- Always use MapStruct for all DTO ↔ Entity conversions. Never write manual field-by-field mapping code.
- Mapper interfaces belong in a `mapper` package within each service.
- Mark all mapper interfaces with `@Mapper(componentModel = "spring")`.

```java
// ✅ GOOD
@Mapper(componentModel = "spring")
public interface CustomerMapper {
    CustomerResponse toResponse(Customer customer);
    Customer toEntity(CreateCustomerRequest request);
}

// ❌ BAD
CustomerResponse response = new CustomerResponse();
response.setFirstName(customer.getFirstName()); // manual mapping
```

## Per-Service Database Registry

| Service | Database Name |
|---|---|
| `identity-service` | `identity_db` |
| `customer-service` | `customer_db` |
| `product-catalog-service` | `product_catalog_db` |
| `order-service` | `order_db` |
| `subscription-service` | `subscription_db` |
| `usage-service` | `usage_db` |
| `billing-service` | `billing_db` |
| `payment-service` | `payment_db` |
| `notification-service` | `notification_db` |
| `ticket-service` | `ticket_db` |

## Redis Usage

- Use Redis for: idempotency key storage, refresh token blacklist, cache-aside for product catalog reads, rate limit counters.
- Always set an explicit TTL when writing to Redis. Never write without expiry.
- Redis access goes through `spring-boot-starter-data-redis` (reactive variant in `api-gateway`).

## Key Domain Entity Fields (Reference)

```
Customer:      id, type[INDIVIDUAL|CORPORATE], firstName, lastName, identityNumber(encrypted), dateOfBirth, status, deletedAt
Order:         id, customerId, status[DRAFT|PENDING_PAYMENT|PAID|FULFILLED|CANCELLED], totalAmount, currency
SagaState:     id, orderId, currentStep, payload, lastUpdated
Subscription:  id, customerId, msisdn, tariffCode, status[ACTIVE|SUSPENDED|TERMINATED], activatedAt
Invoice:       id, customerId, subscriptionId, periodStart, periodEnd, subTotal, tax, grandTotal, status, dueDate
Payment:       id, invoiceId, amount, method, status, externalRef, paidAt
Quota:         id, subscriptionId, periodStart, periodEnd, minutesRemaining, smsRemaining, mbRemaining
Ticket:        id, customerId, category, priority, status, slaDueAt
```
